main event: On March 4, 1950, two civilians reported sighting three luminous objects in the sky over Dubuque, Iowa.
interesting points: The objects were described as being the size of a quarter and traveling at speeds estimated between 1500-2000 mph,The sighting lasted approximately 20 minutes,The objects occasionally blinked on and off before disappearing,One witness, an airline instructor, captured the sighting on film,The objects changed direction and became stationary during the observation.
sighted object: three elliptical and disc-shaped luminous objects
witness description: Two civilian adults driving a car, familiar with reporting sightings
